events.name: Boston Celtics at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 33 points and 11 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder pulled away from the Boston Celtics 105-92 on Sunday for their franchise-record 15th straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33, Thunder top Celtics for franchise-record 15th-straight win

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 25 points, Jarrett Allen had 19 points and 11 rebounds, and the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Charlotte Hornets 115-105 on Sunday night to extend their winning streak to 10.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 25 points, NBA-leading Cavaliers beat Hornets 115-105 for 10th straight win

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 25 points and Dejounte Murray had a triple-double to help the New Orleans Pelicans to a second straight victory over the Washington Wizards, 110-98 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum and Murray lead the Pelicans to a 2nd win in 3 days over the Wizards, 110-98

headlines.description: — Brice Sensabaugh scored 27 points, Collin Sexton added 20 and Walker Kessler grabbed 17 rebounds for the Utah Jazz in a 105-92 win over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah Jazz beat Orlando Magic 105-92 for 2nd win in 2 nights

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 33 points and Fred VanVleet grabbed a key steal late to allow the Houston Rockets to hold on for a 119-115 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green has 33 points, VanVleet's late steal helps Rockets hold on for 119-115 win over Lakers

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Malik Monk had 26 points and 12 assists, Domantas Sabonis contributed 22 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists, and the Sacramento Kings dominated the Golden State Warriors 129-99 on Sunday night for their fourth straight win despite playing without...
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Monk, Domantas Sabonis lead dominant Kings past Stephen Curry and Warriors, 129-99
